# Commit Graph

## Native SCM vs webview

VS Code’s built-in SCM Graph is workbench-native (`scmHistory.ts`), not a webview. SuperGit cannot inherit workbench widgets automatically.

**Theme:** map `--vscode-*` → `--sg-*` in `media/styles.css`; `ThemeProvider` + `readThemeColors()` in `theme.ts`; `MutationObserver` on `data-vscode-theme-kind`. **Do not** add a parallel theme reader from `tokens.ts` in the webview.

**Density:** SuperGit keeps `laneWidth` 22, `rowHeight` 32 (native uses ~11/22). Out of scope: `scmGraph.foreground1–5`, `SourceControlHistoryProvider` API.

## Swimlane topology (parent-driven)

Visual layout follows VS Code’s **swimlane state machine** on `--topo-order` log rows:

| Layer | Module |
|-------|--------|
| Lane assignment | `src/git/swimlanes.ts` — `assignSwimlanes()`; lane columns are **parent-topology only** (not ref labels) |
| Commit fields | `inputSwimlanes` / `outputSwimlanes`, `swimlaneIndex`, `parentSwimlanes[]` on `CommitNode` |
| Renderer | `GraphCanvas` in `CommitTable.tsx` — **per-row** segments at row midline + quadratic arcs (`SWIMLANE_CURVE_RADIUS` ≈ 5px); not node-to-node stair-step beziers |
| Git log | `--topo-order` in `commands.ts` |

Rules:
- Lane 0 = main line; merge second parents open side lanes until branch ends; recycle lanes when possible.
- **No `maxLanes` cap** on active lane count — wide repos need all lanes visible.
- Dynamic graph column: `--graph-column-width` via `graphColumnWidth(laneCount)`; **minimum 80px** so header label does not overflow at 1 lane.
- Merge-parent join-back uses `parentSwimlanes[0]` for first-parent exit paths.
- Render merge-parent **continuation stubs** when an off-page parent would break lane continuity.

## Parser / ref pitfalls

- Pass `remoteNames` into `parseCommits` → `parseRefs` / `parseRemoteRefs` so slash remotes (`foo/bar`) resolve correctly.
- Filter only `${remote}/HEAD` via `isRemoteHeadRef` — **not** plain `HEAD` (needed for checked-out badge).
- Custom remotes like `pil/HEAD` must match exact remote prefix, not substring `includes("/HEAD")`.
- `branch` / ref colors are labels only; lane color comes from swimlane `colorIndex`.

## Commit table columns

Right of description: **Author** (140px), **Date** (`formatRelativeTime`), **Hash** (short SHA + copy icon).

| Concern | Rule |
|---------|------|
| Copy | Icon button → `postMessage({ type: "execute-action", action: "copy-hash", commitHash })`; `stopPropagation` on click |
| Icon UX | Copy icon visible on row hover / selected (like native SCM graph) |
| Scroll | Header inside `.commit-scroll` with `position: sticky; top: 0` so horizontal scroll keeps header + rows aligned |
| Narrow panes | **Do not** use fixed `min-width` + `overflow-x: hidden` — graph pane can be ~280px when detail split is wide. Use `overflow: auto` on `.commit-scroll`, `.commit-table-body { width: max-content; min-width: 100% }`, `.commit-rows { min-width: max-content }` |
| Keyboard | Row is `role="button"` but hash is a nested `<button>`. Gate row `onKeyDown` with `event.target === event.currentTarget` so Enter/Space on copy does not select the row |
| Selection | Only hash is copyable; author/date are display-only. `.app-shell { user-select: none }` is intentional |

Column CSS: `.author-column`, `.date-column`, `.hash-column`; message column `flex: 1; min-width: 0` with ellipsis.

## Graph tab UX (other)

- History scoped via `historyScope` in `App.tsx`; reset pagination on scope change.
- Detail panel: `detailShare` default `0.36`, clamp `0.28`–`0.48`, persisted in webview state.
- File diffs: `vscode.diff` with `preview: false`, `preserveFocus: true`, `ViewColumn.Beside`.
- Dates: list uses `formatRelativeTime()`; detail panel may use `formatFullDate` / `formatShortDate` (`MM/DD HH:mm`).

